## Bootstrap contract

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
- Preferred runtime: project `.venv`
- Fallback runtime: system Python `3.10+`
- `plugin-kit-ai install` does not manage Python dependencies or virtualenv creation
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
- Runtime: system Node.js `20+`
- Commit `package-lock.json` or an equivalent deterministic lockfile for production repos
- TypeScript remains a build-to-JavaScript path over the `node` runtime entrypoint
{{- else if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
- Runtime: POSIX shell on Unix
- On Windows, this runtime requires `bash` in `PATH`
- `plugin-kit-ai install` does not package or distribute shell runtime dependencies
{{- end }}

## Build

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
. .venv/bin/activate
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex --strict
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
```bash
npm install
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex --strict
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
```bash
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex --strict
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```
{{- end }}

## Codex

1. Put repository instructions in `AGENTS.md`.
2. Keep project-local Codex settings in `.codex/config.toml`.
3. The generated executable handles the documented `notify` hook.

Hook output on stdout must stay reserved for Codex wire responses. Write diagnostics to stderr only.
Do not write debug logs or human-readable status lines to stdout.
